{"title":"Perf memoization: skipTo cache analysis","gitnotes":1,"type":"markdown","body":"## Summary\n\nRepeated `skipTo('gitnotes')` + `skipTo('body')` on the same tokenizer rescanned the full input. WeakMap cache keys by tokenizer instance — no leak across parses.\n\n### Benchmark (synthetic 32 KB envelope, 1000 parses)\n\n| Approach | p50 | p99 |\n|----------|----:|----:|\n| naive skipTo | 4.8 ms | 12.1 ms |\n| skipToCached | 0.9 ms | 2.4 ms |\n\n### Diff highlights\n\n- [WeakMap cache layer](gitnotes:diff/examples/demo/parser/src/parser.ts#R4-R4) — module-level, GC-friendly.\n- [skipToCached](gitnotes:diff/examples/demo/parser/src/parser.ts#R36-R45) — short-circuit on hit.\n- [skipTo loop bound](gitnotes:diff/examples/demo/parser/src/parser.ts#R47-R55) — eof escape hatch.\n\n- [x] No API change\n- [x] Memory bounded per parse\n- [ ] Cache invalidation N/A (tokenizer is single-pass)\n\n> Acceptable trade-off: first lookup still O(n); second field lookup is O(1) skip."}
